
[1]drachma

   DRACHMA, n. [L., Gr.]

   1. A Grecian coin. Of the value of seven pence, three farthings,
   sterling, or nearly fourteen cents.

   2. The eighth part of an ounce, or sixty grains, or three scruples; a
   weight used by apothecaries, but usually written dram.
